verses.roman:
govinda-dvārā prabhura śeṣa-prasāda pāilā
preme matta dui-jana nācite lāgilā

synonyms: govinda-dvārā—through Govinda; prabhura—of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; śeṣa-prasāda—remnants of food; pāilā—they got; preme matta—overwhelmed by ecstasy; dui-jana—both of them; nācite lāgilā—began to dance.
translation: When they received the remnants of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu's prasāda through Govinda, they respected it, and then they both began to dance in ecstasy.
